cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on scheduling in wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the inter-user interference and multiplexing gains in full-duplex systems, which are concepts related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes scheduling strategies to manage interference and optimize system utility, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions delay-sensitive applications, which are often related to multimedia systems. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper introduces practical construction algorithms for scheduling, which can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence techniques.
